🔹 1️⃣ Task
Kya hai:-
Task ek chhota unit of work hota hai jo workflow ya system me execute hota hai.
Ye usually single purpose ke liye hota hai: jaise role assign karna, approval check karna, email bhejna, etc.
WorkItem ya Workflow ke andar multiple tasks ho sakte hain.

Example:-
RoleAssignmentTask → ek identity ko role assign kare.
ProvisioningTask → user ke liye account create kare.

Key points:-
Task specific action karta hai.
Task ko workflow ya job ke andar schedule / launch kiya jata hai.
Ye generally short-lived hota hai.


🔹 2️⃣ Job:-
Kya hai:-
Job ek bada unit of work ya scheduled execution hota hai.
Ye ek ya multiple tasks ka collection hota hai jo ek saath execute hote hain.
Mostly background / periodic process ke liye hota hai.

Example:-
IdentityRefreshJob → saare identities ko daily refresh kare.
AccessCertificationJob → access review workflow trigger kare for multiple users.

Key points:-
Job usually scheduled / automated hota hai (daily, weekly, etc.).
Job me multiple tasks ho sakte hain.
Long-running aur system-wide impact wale processes ke liye use hota hai.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Task Types:-
Task ka type define karta hai ki task kaise execute hota hai:-
Type	                      Description
Scheduled:---------------Ye task automatic schedule ke through run hota hai.
Manual:------------------Ye task manually trigger hota hai user ya admin se.
Event:-------------------Ye kisi event ke hone par trigger hota hai (jaise identity creation).
Provisioning:------------Specific provisioning task ke liye.
Aggregation:-------------Data aggregation ya import ke liye task.
Notification:------------Notification send karne ke liye task.

2️⃣ Task Status:-
Task ka status indicate karta hai ki task abhi kaise perform ho raha hai:-
Status	             Description
Pending:--------Task scheduled hai, lekin abhi run nahi hua.
Running:--------Task currently execute ho raha hai.
Completed:------Task successfully execute ho chuka hai.
Failed:---------Task execute nahi ho paya, koi error hua.
Cancelled:------Task ko cancel kar diya gaya execution se pehle.
Rejected:-------Task kisi reason se reject kar diya gaya (e.g., validation failure).
Archived:-------Task complete hone ke baad archive ho gaya.

Task Escalation Levels:-
Escalation Level	               Meaning / Use Case
0	               No Escalation – Task ko escalate nahi kiya jayega
1	               First Level Escalation – First approver / owner ke liye
2	               Second Level Escalation – Agar first level approve nahi karta
3	               Third Level Escalation – Higher authority / manager
4	               Fourth Level Escalation – Very high level, e.g., Head / Director
5	               Fifth Level Escalation – Top management (rarely used)
