1️⃣ getId():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka unique identifier (ID) return karta hai.
Type: String
Example:-
Task myTask = new Task();
myTask.setName("Sample Task");
System.out.println("Task ID: " + myTask.getId());

Output:-
Task ID: 12345-abcde (example ID generated by SailPoint)

2️⃣ getName():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka naam return karta hai.
Example:-
Task myTask = new Task();
myTask.setName("Data Cleanup");
System.out.println("Task Name: " + myTask.getName());

Output:-
Task Name: Data Cleanup

3️⃣ getType():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka type return karta hai. Ye Scheduled ya Manual ho sakta hai.
Example:-
Task myTask = new Task();
myTask.setType("Scheduled");
System.out.println("Task Type: " + myTask.getType());

Output:-
Task Type: Scheduled

4️⃣ getOwner():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka owner (Identity object) return karta hai.
Example:-
