1️⃣ launch():-
Kya karta hai: Task ko immediately execute karta hai.
Use case: Jab tu chahta hai ki task abhi run ho jaaye, scheduled wait ke bina.

Task myTask = new Task();
myTask.launch(); // task start ho gaya

2️⃣ schedule():-
Kya karta hai: Task ko future ke liye schedule karta hai.
Use case: Agar tu chahta hai task kisi specific time ya interval pe run ho.

Task myTask = new Task();
myTask.schedule(); // task future me run hoga
Real system me schedule ke liye cron expression ya timing bhi pass karte hain.

3️⃣ cancel():-
Kya karta hai: Task execution ko rokti hai agar wo abhi running hai ya future ke liye scheduled hai.

Use case: Agar task galat schedule hua ya cancel karna hai.
myTask.cancel(); // task ab run nahi hoga

4️⃣ archive():-
Kya karta hai: Task complete hone ke baad archive kar deta hai.

Use case: Task ke record ko future reference ke liye save karna.
myTask.archive(); // task ka record store ho gaya

5️⃣ complete():-
Kya karta hai: Task ko manual completion mark karta hai.

Use case: Agar task successfully finish ho gaya aur manually update karna hai.
myTask.complete(); // task status = Completed

6️⃣ reject():-
Kya karta hai: Task ko reject mark karta hai.

Use case: Agar task invalid hai ya validation fail hua.
myTask.reject(); // task status = Rejected

2️⃣ clone():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka exact copy create karta hai.
Use case: Agar same task ko multiple targets ke liye use karna ho.
Task newTask = (Task) myTask.clone();
System.out.println("Cloned Task Name: " + newTask.getName());

3️⃣ equals(Object obj):-
Kya karta hai: Check karta hai ki do Task objects equal hain ya nahi.
Use case: Task comparison, duplicate check.

Task anotherTask = new Task();
anotherTask.setName("Cleanup Task");

if(myTask.equals(anotherTask)) {
    System.out.println("Tasks are equal");
} else {
    System.out.println("Tasks are different");
}

4️⃣ hashCode():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka unique hash code return karta hai.
Use case: Hash-based collections me store karne ke liye.
System.out.println("Task HashCode: " + myTask.hashCode());

5️⃣ toString():-
Kya karta hai: Task ka string representation return karta hai.
Use case: Debugging ya logs me use hota hai.
System.out.println(myTask.toString());

6️⃣ getLogs() & addLog(String log):-
Kya karta hai: Task ke logs ko fetch / add karta hai.
Use case: Execution history track karna.

myTask.addLog("Task started at 9:00 AM");
myTask.addLog("Task finished at 9:05 AM");
System.out.println("Logs: " + myTask.getLogs());

Output:-
Logs: [Task started at 9:00 AM, Task finished at 9:05 AM]

7️⃣ getMessages() & addMessage(String msg):-
Kya karta hai: Task ke messages ko fetch / add karta hai.
Use case: UI ya workflow me messages show karna.

myTask.addMessage("Task requires approval");
myTask.addMessage("Task approved by Admin");
System.out.println("Messages: " + myTask.getMessages());

Output:-
Messages: [Task requires approval, Task approved by Admin]
