()validate() Task class me ek bohot important method hai,aur iska kaam hai task ki poori configuration aur dependencies check karna.
Main ab har cheez step by step bata raha hoon jo validate() check karta hai.

1️⃣ Mandatory Fields Check:-
Task ke liye kuch fields mandatory hote hain. validate() ensure karta hai ki ye set hain:
name → Task ka naam hona chahiye
type → Task type set hona chahiye (Scheduled, Manual, etc.)
target → Agar task target-based hai, target object valid hona chahiye
owner → Task ka owner set hona chahiye (Identity)

Example:-
if(task.getName() == null) throw new ValidationException("Task name missing");
if(task.getType() == null) throw new ValidationException("Task type missing");
if(task.getTarget() == null) throw new ValidationException("Target object missing");

2️⃣ Target Object Validation:-
validate() check karta hai ki target object valid hai ya nahi.
Target ka type check hota hai: Identity, Application, CustomObject, etc.
Agar target me required fields missing hain → validation fail ho jata hai.

Example:-
if(task.getTarget() instanceof Identity) {
    Identity id = (Identity) task.getTarget();
    if(id.getName() == null) throw new ValidationException("Identity target name missing");
}

3️⃣ Task Arguments Validation:-
Task ke arguments / parameters check hote hain:-
Mandatory arguments exist karte hain ya nahi
Argument types correct hain ya nahi

Example:-
Map<String,Object> args = task.getArguments();
if(args != null && !args.containsKey("priority"))
    throw new ValidationException("priority argument missing");
	
4️⃣ Execution Configuration Check:-
validate() ye bhi ensure karta hai ki task schedule/execution settings valid hain:-
Start time / cron expression sahi hai
Dependencies (agar task kisi aur task pe depend karta hai) properly set hain
Recurrence / frequency correct hai

5️⃣ Owner/Permissions Check:-
Task ka owner valid hona chahiye aur task ko execute karne ka permission/role hona chahiye.

6️⃣ Status & Result Fields Check:-
Task ke status aur result fields proper initial value set kiye hain ya nahi.
Example: Scheduled task me ExecutionStatus default Pending hona chahiye

7️⃣ Optional Checks:-
Task me custom validations bhi ho sakti hain:-
Target object specific fields check
Task specific rules (e.g., Identity target ka email set hai ya nahi).
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ getWorkItems():-
Kya karta hai: Task ke saare work items return karta hai (pending + completed).
Return type: List<WorkItem>
List<WorkItem> allItems = myTask.getWorkItems();
System.out.println("All Work Items: " + allItems.size());

2️⃣ getPendingWorkItems():-
Kya karta hai: Task ke sirf pending work items return karta hai (jo abhi complete nahi hue).
List<WorkItem> pendingItems = myTask.getPendingWorkItems();
System.out.println("Pending Work Items: " + pendingItems.size());

3️⃣ getCompletedWorkItems():-
Kya karta hai: Task ke completed work items return karta hai.
List<WorkItem> completedItems = myTask.getCompletedWorkItems();
System.out.println("Completed Work Items: " + completedItems.size());

4️⃣ getWorkItemById(String id):-
Kya karta hai: Specific WorkItem ko uske ID ke basis pe fetch karta hai.
WorkItem wi = myTask.getWorkItemById("WI123");
System.out.println("Work Item: " + wi.getId() + " Status: " + wi.getStatus());

5️⃣ getApprovalSet() & setApprovalSet(ApprovalSet approvalSet):-
Kya karta hai: Task ke ApprovalSet ko get/set karta hai.
ApprovalSet: Ek object jo task me approval workflow ke details store karta hai (approvers, status, hierarchy).
ApprovalSet approval = myTask.getApprovalSet();
myTask.setApprovalSet(approval);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6️⃣ getWorkItemConfig() & setWorkItemConfig(WorkItemConfig config):-
Kya karta hai: Task ke WorkItem configuration ko get/set karta hai.
WorkItemConfig: Ye define karta hai ki work item kaise create, assign aur process hoga (e.g., due date, escalation).
WorkItemConfig config = myTask.getWorkItemConfig();
myTask.setWorkItemConfig(config);

Java Example – WorkItemConfig with Task
import java.util.Date;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

// Simulate WorkItemConfig class
class WorkItemConfig {
    private int dueDays;
    private String escalation;

    public WorkItemConfig() {}

    public WorkItemConfig(int dueDays, String escalation) {
        this.dueDays = dueDays;
        this.escalation = escalation;
    }

    public int getDueDays() { return dueDays; }
    public void setDueDays(int dueDays) { this.dueDays = dueDays; }

    public String getEscalation() { return escalation; }
    public void setEscalation(String escalation) { this.escalation = escalation; }

    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return "WorkItemConfig [dueDays=" + dueDays + ", escalation=" + escalation + "]";
    }
}

// Simulate Task class
class Task {
    private String name;
    private WorkItemConfig workItemConfig;

    public Task(String name) { this.name = name; }

    // WorkItemConfig getters/setters
    public WorkItemConfig getWorkItemConfig() { return workItemConfig; }
    public void setWorkItemConfig(WorkItemConfig config) { this.workItemConfig = config; }

    public String getName() { return name; }
}

public class TaskDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create Task
        Task myTask = new Task("Approval Task");

        // Create WorkItemConfig
        WorkItemConfig config = new WorkItemConfig();
        config.setDueDays(5);
        config.setEscalation("Manager");

        // Set WorkItemConfig to Task
        myTask.setWorkItemConfig(config);

        // Get WorkItemConfig from Task
        WorkItemConfig retrievedConfig = myTask.getWorkItemConfig();

        // Print result
        System.out.println("Task Name: " + myTask.getName());
        System.out.println("WorkItemConfig: " + retrievedConfig);
        System.out.println("Due Days: " + retrievedConfig.getDueDays());
        System.out.println("Escalation: " + retrievedConfig.getEscalation());
    }
}
Sample Output:-
Task Name: Approval Task
WorkItemConfig: WorkItemConfig [dueDays=5, escalation=Manager]
Due Days: 5
Escalation: Manager
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ getIdentityRequestId() & setIdentityRequestId(String id);-
Kya karta hai:-
Ye method task se associated identity request ka ID get/set karta hai.
IdentityRequest = ek object jo user ka access request / role request represent karta hai.

myTask.setIdentityRequestId("IR12345");
System.out.println("Identity Request ID: " + myTask.getIdentityRequestId());
Output:-
Identity Request ID: IR12345

2️⃣ getCaseId() & setCaseId(String id):-
Kya karta hai:-
Ye workflow case ka ID get/set karta hai.

myTask.setCaseId("WC67890");
System.out.println("Workflow Case ID: " + myTask.getCaseId());
Output:-
Workflow Case ID: WC67890

3️⃣ getWorkflowCase() & setWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase wc):-
Kya karta hai:-
Task ke associated WorkflowCase object ko get/set karta hai.
WorkflowCase me work items, approvals, escalations store hote hain.

WorkflowCase wc = new WorkflowCase("WC67890");
myTask.setWorkflowCase(wc);
System.out.println("Workflow Case Object ID: " + myTask.getWorkflowCase().getId());

4️⃣ getEscalationDate() & setEscalationDate(Date date):-
Kya karta hai:-
Task ke escalation date/time ko get/set karta hai.
Agar task pending rahe aur auto-escalate karna ho to ye date important hai.

Date escalation = new Date(); // current date/time
myTask.setEscalationDate(escalation);
System.out.println("Escalation Date: " + myTask.getEscalationDate());

1️⃣ getEscalationLevel() & setEscalationLevel(int level):-
Kya karta hai:-
Task ke escalation hierarchy level ko get/set karta hai.
Level 1 = first level approver, Level 2 = second level, and so on.

myTask.setEscalationLevel(2);
System.out.println("Escalation Level: " + myTask.getEscalationLevel());

Output:-
Escalation Level: 2

2️⃣ getEscalationOwner() & setEscalationOwner(Identity owner):-
Kya karta hai:-
Task ke current escalation owner ko get/set karta hai.
Escalation owner = wo person jiske paas task auto-escalate hone par jayega.

// Simulate Identity class
class Identity {
    private String name;
    public Identity(String name) { this.name = name; }
    public String getName() { return name; }
}

Identity owner = new Identity("Manager John");
myTask.setEscalationOwner(owner);
System.out.println("Escalation Owner: " + myTask.getEscalationOwner().getName());

Output:-
Escalation Owner: Manager John

3️⃣ getReminders() & setReminders(List<Date> reminders) & addReminder(Date date):-
Kya karta hai:-
Task ke reminder dates ko manage karta hai.
setReminders() → poori list set karna
addReminder() → ek date add karna
getReminders() → list of all reminder dates.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.TaskManager;
import sailpoint.object.Task;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.object.WorkflowCase;
import sailpoint.object.ApprovalSet;
import sailpoint.object.WorkItemConfig;
import sailpoint.object.WorkItem;

import java.util.Date;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;

public class TaskExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        SailPointContext context = null;
        try {
            // 🔹 Get SailPoint context from Factory
            context = SailPointFactory.createContext();

            // 🔹 Load existing Task by name or ID
            String taskName = "Access Certification Task";
            Task task = context.getObject(Task.class, taskName);

            if (task == null) {
                System.out.println("Task not found: " + taskName);
                return;
            }

            // ============================================
            // 1️⃣ Basic Info
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Task ID: " + task.getId());
            System.out.println("Task Name: " + task.getName());
            System.out.println("Task Type: " + task.getType());

            Identity owner = task.getOwner();
            System.out.println("Task Owner: " + (owner != null ? owner.getName() : "None"));

            // ============================================
            // 2️⃣ Task Status / Lifecycle
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Current Status: " + task.getStatus());

            // Launch immediately
            TaskManager.launch(task, context);
            System.out.println("Task Launched");

            // Update status manually
            task.setStatus(Task.STATUS_RUNNING);
            System.out.println("Status After Launch: " + task.getStatus());

            // Cancel Task
            TaskManager.cancel(task, context);
            System.out.println("Task Cancelled");

            // Complete Task
            task.setStatus(Task.STATUS_COMPLETED);
            System.out.println("Task Marked Completed");

            // Reject Task
            task.setStatus(Task.STATUS_REJECTED);
            System.out.println("Task Rejected");

            // Archive Task
            TaskManager.archive(task, context);
            System.out.println("Task Archived");

            // Commit changes
            context.commitTransaction();

            // ============================================
            // 3️⃣ Audit / Metadata
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Created On: " + task.getCreated());
            System.out.println("Modified On: " + task.getModified());

            if (task.getCreatedBy() != null)
                System.out.println("Created By: " + task.getCreatedBy().getName());

            if (task.getModifiedBy() != null)
                System.out.println("Modified By: " + task.getModifiedBy().getName());

            // ============================================
            // 4️⃣ Target Info
            // ============================================
            Object target = task.getTarget();
            System.out.println("Target: " + (target != null ? target.toString() : "None"));
            System.out.println("Target Name: " + task.getTargetName());
            System.out.println("Target Type: " + task.getTargetType());

            // ============================================
            // 5️⃣ Arguments & Execution Info
            // ============================================
            Map<String,Object> argsMap = task.getArguments();
            System.out.println("Arguments: " + argsMap);

            System.out.println("Execution Time: " + task.getExecutionTime());
            System.out.println("Execution Result: " + task.getExecutionResult());
            System.out.println("Execution Status: " + task.getExecutionStatus());

            // ============================================
            // 6️⃣ Validation & Utilities
            // ============================================
            boolean valid = task.validate();
            System.out.println("Is Task Valid? " + valid);

            System.out.println("Task toString(): " + task.toString());

            // ============================================
            // 7️⃣ Logs & Messages
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Logs: " + task.getLogs());
            task.addLog("Checked task details at " + new Date());

            System.out.println("Messages: " + task.getMessages());
            task.addMessage("Task inspected programmatically");

            // ============================================
            // 8️⃣ Work Items (Workflow)
            // ============================================
            List<WorkItem> allItems = task.getWorkItems();
            System.out.println("Total WorkItems: " + allItems.size());

            List<WorkItem> pendingItems = task.getPendingWorkItems();
            System.out.println("Pending WorkItems: " + pendingItems.size());

            List<WorkItem> completedItems = task.getCompletedWorkItems();
            System.out.println("Completed WorkItems: " + completedItems.size());

            // Get specific WorkItem by ID
            WorkItem wi = task.getWorkItemById("WI12345");
            System.out.println("WorkItem WI12345: " + wi);

            // ============================================
            // 9️⃣ Approval & WorkItem Config
            // ============================================
            ApprovalSet approvalSet = task.getApprovalSet();
            System.out.println("Approval Set: " + approvalSet);

            WorkItemConfig workConfig = task.getWorkItemConfig();
            System.out.println("WorkItem Config: " + workConfig);

            // ============================================
            // 10️⃣ Workflow Case / Identity Request
            // ============================================
            String identityReqId = task.getIdentityRequestId();
            System.out.println("Identity Request ID: " + identityReqId);

            String caseId = task.getCaseId();
            System.out.println("Workflow Case ID: " + caseId);

            WorkflowCase wc = task.getWorkflowCase();
            System.out.println("Workflow Case Object: " + wc);

            // ============================================
            // 11️⃣ Escalation Info
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Escalation Date: " + task.getEscalationDate());
            System.out.println("Escalation Level: " + task.getEscalationLevel());

            Identity escalationOwner = task.getEscalationOwner();
            System.out.println("Escalation Owner: " + (escalationOwner != null ? escalationOwner.getName() : "None"));

            System.out.println("Reminders: " + task.getReminders());

            context.commitTransaction();

        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();

        } finally {
            if (context != null) {
                context.decache(true);
                context.close();
            }
        }
    }
}